regard as unproductive. At the same time, law firm partners continue to seek the non-financial rewards of being members of a distinct profession and are sensitive to whether their firms are committed to providing them. Regan and Rohrer argue that modern firms responding effectively to business demands while credibly affirming the importance of non-financial professional values can create strong cultures that enhance their ability to weather the storms of the modern legal market.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aLaw firmszUnited States. 0aLaw firms-United States. 0aPractice of lawzUnited States. 0aPractice of law-United States. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  abusiness of law.  alaw firms.  alegal ethics.  alegal profession.  alegal services.  aprofessions.1 aRohrer, Lisa H., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishz978311070486008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020z9783110704587oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226742274423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226742274/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070486-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020